n- `it('rewrites relative link URLs to /assets/ path')` - `./doc.pdf` → `/assets/doc.pdf`\n- `it('leaves absolute URLs unchanged')` - `https://cdn.example.com/image.png` stays unchanged\n- `it('generates asset manifest in ctx.data')` - Creates `asset-manifest` with assets array\n- `it('handles files with no asset references')` - Content unchanged\n- `it('handles multiple assets in one file')` - Rewrites all src/href attributes\n- `it('asset manifest includes all discovered assets')` - Accumulates across multiple files\n- `it('does not double-process already-rewritten URLs')` - Skips URLs already starting with `/assets/`\n\n**Asset Manifest Structure:**\n```typescript\ninterface AssetManifest {\n  assets: string[];  // list of asset filenames\n}\n```\n\n**Expected Plugin Behavior:**\n- Implements `transformContent` hook\n- Rewrites relative URLs (`./path`) to `/assets/path`\n- Preserves absolute URLs\n- Creates/updates asset manifest in ctx.data\n- Tracks all assets across files\n\n---\n\n### 15. **tests/plugins/syntax-highlight.test.ts** (Full Contents - 108 lines)\n\n**Syntax Highlight Plugin Tests:**\n- `it('adds language class to code blocks')` - `class=\"language-javascript\"` → `class=\"language-javascript highlighted\"`\n- `it('adds data-language attribute to pre tags')` - Adds `data-language=\"python\"` to `<pre>` tag\n- `it('handles multiple code blocks in one file')` - Processes all code blocks independently\n- `it('handles code block with no language specified')` - Leaves plain `<code>` blocks unchanged\n- `it('adds highlighted class to processed blocks')` - Only blocks with language class get 'highlighted'\n- `it('preserves code block content')` - Code content unchanged\n- `it('handles empty code blocks')` - Processes even if empty\n- `it('does not modify inline code')` - Only processes `<pre><code>`, not `<code>` tags alone\n\n**Expected Plugin Behavior:**\n- Implements `transformContent` hook\n- Targets `<pre><code class=\"language-*\">` blocks\n- Adds 'highlighted' class to the code element\n- Adds `data-language=\"*\"` attribute to the pre element\n- Ignores blocks without language class\n- Leaves inline code untouched\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThis is an **SSG (Static Site Generator) Toolkit** with a **DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph) plugin system**. The architecture features:\n\n1. **Core System** (src/core/):\n   - Type definitions for configuration, content, build context, plugins, and templates\n   - BuildEngine with topological sort for plugin dependency resolution\n   - Built-in templates (default article layout, list layout)\n   - 4-phase build process: beforeBuild → transformContent → template rendering → afterBuild\n\n2. **Plugin System** (tests/plugins/):\n   - **search-index**: Generates searchable index JSON\n   - **markdown-ext**: Markdown to HTML conversion with footnotes and admonitions\n   - **taxonomy**: Tag-based content organization and listing pages\n   - **dev-server**: Development server configuration\n   - **rss-feed**: RSS 2.0 feed generation\n   - **sitemap**: XML sitemap generation\n   - **asset-pipeline**: Asset URL rewriting and manifest generation\n   - **syntax-highlight**: Code block syntax highlighting\n\nAll plugins are designed to be composable and can depend on other plugins while maintaining correct execution order."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a0035b8 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 36658\ntool_uses: 18\nduration_ms: 51856</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0c0876a9-0499-47ee-b17e-658fa944a2e8","uuid":"531e45e3-aca5-4f63-b5a8-34f7297af450","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the codebase at /workspace. I need to understand:\n\n1. The full directory structure\n2. The Plugin interface from src/core/types.ts\n3. The build engine in src/core/\n4. All existing tests in tests/core.test.ts\n5. ALL plugin test files in tests/plugins/ - read every single one completely\n6. package.json for dependencies and scripts\n7. tsconfig.json for TypeScript configuration\n\nRead every file completely. I need full contents of:\n- src/core/types.ts\n- src/core/engine.ts  \n- src/core/templates.ts (if exists)\n- tests/core.test.ts\n- Every file in tests/plugins/\n- package.json\n- tsconfig.json\n\nBe very thorough - read all files completely and report their full contents.","agentId":"a0035b8","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have now thoroughly explored the entire codebase. Here is my complete analysis:\n\n## Complete Codebase Analysis\n\n### Directory Structure\n```\n/workspace/\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n├── src/\n│   └── core/\n│       ├── index.ts\n│       ├── types.ts\n│       ├── engine.ts\n│       └── templates.ts\n└── tests/\n    ├── core.test.ts\n    └── plugins/\n        ├── asset-pipeline.test.ts\n        ├── dev-server.test.ts\n        ├── markdown-ext.test.ts\n        ├── rss-feed.test.ts\n        ├── search-index.test.ts\n        ├── sitemap.test.ts\n        ├── syntax-highlight.test.ts\n        └── taxonomy.test.ts\n```\n\n---\n\n### 1. **package.json** (Full Contents)\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-ssg-toolkit\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"SSG Toolkit benchmark - static site generator with DAG plugin system\",\n  \"main\": \"dist/core/index.js\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"keywords\": [],\n  \"author\": \"\",\n  \"license\": \"ISC\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.57.1\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.9.3\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.1.9\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@types/express\": \"^5.0.6\",\n    \"@types/marked\": \"^5.0.2\",\n    \"express\": \"^5.2.1\",\n    \"marked\": \"^17.0.2\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key Details:**\n- ES modules configuration\n- TypeScript 5.9.3 with strict mode\n- Vitest 2.1.9 for testing\n- Express and Marked as core dependencies\n- Build output: `dist/core/index.js`\n\n---\n\n### 2. **tsconfig.json** (Full Contents)\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"]\n}\n```\n\n**Configuration:**\n- ES2022 target with strict TypeScript\n- Node16 module resolution\n- Declaration files generated\n- Root: `src/`, Output: `dist/`\n\n---\n\n### 3. **src/core/types.ts** (Full Contents)\n```typescript\nexport interface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;        // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\nexport interface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n**Type System Overview:**\n- **SiteConfig**: Site metadata and directory paths\n- **ContentFile**: Individual content with slug, title, content, metadata, optional date, tags, and template specification\n- **BuildContext**: State during build with files, output map, assets map, and shared data store\n- **PluginHooks**: Three lifecycle points - beforeBuild, transformContent (per-file), afterBuild\n- **Plugin**: Named plugin with version, dependencies array, and hooks\n- **Template**: Simple renderer function with name and render method\n\n---\n\n### 4. **src/core/engine.ts** (Full Contents)\n```typescript\nimport { BuildContext, ContentFile, Plugin, SiteConfig, Template } from './types.js';\n\nexport class BuildEngine {\n  private plugins: Plugin[] = [];\n  private templates: Map<string, Template> = new Map();\n\n  constructor(private config: SiteConfig) {}\n\n  registerPlugin(plugin: Plugin): void {\n    this.plugins.push(plugin);\n  }\n\n  registerTemplate(template: Template): void {\n    this.templates.set(template.name, template);\n  }\n\n  // Resolve plugin execution order using topological sort\n  resolvePluginOrder(): Plugin[] {\n    const sorted: Plugin[] = [];\n    const visited = new Set<string>();\n    const visiting = new Set<string>();\n    const pluginMap = new Map(this.plugins.map(p => [p.name, p]));\n\n    const visit = (name: string) => {\n      if (visited.has(name)) return;\n      if (visiting.has(name)) {\n        throw new Error(`Circular dependency detected: ${name}`);\n      }\n      visiting.add(name);\n      const plugin = pluginMap.get(name);\n      if (plugin) {\n        for (const dep of plugin.dependencies) {\n          if (!pluginMap.has(dep)) {\n            throw new Error(`Missing dependency: ${name} requires ${dep}`);\n          }\n          visit(dep);\n        }\n      }\n      visiting.delete(name);\n      visited.add(name);\n      if (plugin) sorted.push(plugin);\n    };\n\n    for (const plugin of this.plugins) {\n      visit(plugin.name);\n    }\n    return sorted;\n  }\n\n  async build(files: ContentFile[]): Promise<BuildContext> {\n    const ctx: BuildContext = {\n      config: this.config,\n      files: [...files],\n      output: new Map(),\n      assets: new Map(),\n      data: new Map(),\n    };\n\n    const orderedPlugins = this.resolvePluginOrder();\n\n    // beforeBuild hooks\n    for (const plugin of orderedPlugins) {\n      if (plugin.hooks.beforeBuild) {\n        await plugin.hooks.beforeBuild(ctx);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // transformContent hooks (applied to each file in plugin order)\n    for (const plugin of orderedPlugins) {\n      if (plugin.hooks.transformContent) {\n        const transformed: ContentFile[] = [];\n        for (const file of ctx.files) {\n          transformed.push(await plugin.hooks.transformContent(file, ctx));\n        }\n        ctx.files = transformed;\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Render templates\n    for (const file of ctx.files) {\n      const templateName = file.template || 'default';\n      const template = this.templates.get(templateName);\n      if (template) {\n        const rendered = template.render(file.content, {\n          title: file.title,\n          slug: file.slug,\n          date: file.date,\n          tags: file.tags,\n          ...file.metadata,\n          siteTitle: this.config.title,\n          baseUrl: this.config.baseUrl,\n        });\n        ctx.output.set(`${file.slug}.html`, rendered);\n      } else {\n        ctx.output.set(`${file.slug}.html`, file.content);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // afterBuild hooks\n    for (const plugin of orderedPlugins) {\n      if (plugin.hooks.afterBuild) {\n        await plugin.hooks.afterBuild(ctx);\n      }\n    }\n\n    return ctx;\n  }\n\n  getPlugins(): Plugin[] {\n    return [...this.plugins];\n  }\n\n  getTemplates(): Map<string, Template> {\n    return new Map(this.templates);\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Build Engine Features:**\n- **Plugin Registration**: `registerPlugin()` and `registerTemplate()` methods\n- **Topological Sort**: `resolvePluginOrder()` uses DFS to order plugins by dependencies with cycle detection\n- **Build Process** (4 phases):\n  1. beforeBuild hooks in dependency order\n  2. transformContent hooks applied file-by-file in plugin order\n  3. Template rendering (uses file.template or 'default')\n  4. afterBuild hooks in dependency order\n- **Error Handling**: Detects circular dependencies and missing dependencies\n- **Getter Methods**: Return copies to prevent external mutation\n\n---\n\n### 5. **src/core/templates.ts** (Full Contents)\n```typescript\nimport { Template } from './types.js';\n\nexport function createDefaultTemplate(): Template {\n  return {\n    name: 'default',\n    render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => {\n      return `<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>${data.title || ''} | ${data.siteTitle || ''}</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <article>\n    <h1>${data.title || ''}</h1>\n    ${data.date ? `<time>${data.date}</time>` : ''}\n    <div class=\"content\">${content}</div>\n  </article>\n</body>\n</html>`;\n    }\n  };\n}\n\nexport function createListTemplate(): Template {\n  return {\n    name: 'list',\n    render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => {\n      return `<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>${data.title || ''} | ${data.siteTitle || ''}</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>${data.title || ''}</h1>\n  <div class=\"list\">${content}</div>\n</body>\n</html>`;\n    }\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Built-in Templates:**\n- **Default Template**: Article layout with title, optional date, and content\n- **List Template**: List-oriented layout with title and list container\n- Both include DOCTYPE and proper HTML structure with site title in page title\n\n---\n\n### 6. **src/core/index.ts** (Full Contents)\n```typescript\nexport { BuildEngine } from './engine.js';\nexport { createDefaultTemplate, createListTemplate } from './templates.js';\nexport type { BuildContext, 