+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KCUQuEENkbVRX3CJQ9WVyM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QdZN73V6St8YeSzo2E2eth","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-ssg-plugins.md","content":"# SSG Toolkit Plugins Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Implement 8 plugins for the SSG toolkit, organized in 3 dependency waves, passing all 60 plugin tests.\n\n**Architecture:** Each plugin exports a `createXxxPlugin()` factory returning a `Plugin` object with name, version, dependencies array, and hooks. Plugins use `transformContent` for per-file transforms (markdown-ext, asset-pipeline, syntax-highlight) and `beforeBuild`/`afterBuild` for index building (taxonomy, rss-feed, search-index, sitemap, dev-server). Plugins communicate via `ctx.data` shared store.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript (strict, ES2022, Node16 modules), `marked` library for markdown, Vitest for testing.\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Create `src/plugins/markdown-ext.ts`\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/plugins/markdown-ext.ts`\n- Test: `tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts` (already exists)\n\n**Step 1: Implement the plugin**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Plugin, ContentFile, BuildContext } from '../core/types.js';\nimport { marked } from 'marked';\n\nfunction processFootnotes(content: string): string {\n  const footnoteDefRegex = /^\\[\\^(\\d+)\\]:\\s*(.+)$/gm;\n  const footnotes: { id: string; text: string }[] = [];\n  let processed = content.replace(footnoteDefRegex, (_match, id, text) => {\n    footnotes.push({ id, text });\n    return '';\n  });\n\n  processed = processed.replace(/\\[\\^(\\d+)\\]/g, '<sup><a href=\"#fn-$1\">$1</a></sup>');\n\n  if (footnotes.length > 0) {\n    const footnotesSection = `<section class=\"footnotes\"><ol>${footnotes.map(f => `<li id=\"fn-${f.id}\">${f.text}</li>`).join('')}</ol></section>`;\n    processed += footnotesSection;\n  }\n\n  return processed;\n}\n\nfunction processAdmonitions(content: string): string {\n  return content.replace(/^:::(note|warning|tip)\\n([\\s\\S]*?)^:::/gm, (_match, type, body) => {\n    return `<div class=\"admonition admonition-${type}\">\\n${body.trim()}\\n</div>`;\n  });\n}\n\nexport function createMarkdownExtPlugin(): Plugin {\n  return {\n    name: 'markdown-ext',\n    version: '1.0.0',\n    dependencies: [],\n    hooks: {\n      transformContent: (file: ContentFile, _ctx: BuildContext): ContentFile => {\n        let content = file.content;\n        content = processAdmonitions(content);\n        content = processFootnotes(content);\n        content = marked.parse(content, { async: false }) as string;\n        return { ...file, content };\n      },\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Key details:**\n- Process admonitions FIRST (before markdown), then footnotes, then run `marked.parse()`\n- Footnote references: `[^1]` → `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>`\n- Footnote defs: `[^1]: text` → collected and appended as `<section class=\"footnotes\">` with `<li id=\"fn-1\">`\n- Admonitions: `:::type\\ncontent\\n:::` → `<div class=\"admonition admonition-type\">`\n- marked.parse() is sync with `{ async: false }`\n\n**Step 2: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts\n```\n\nExpected: 8 tests pass.\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Create `src/plugins/asset-pipeline.ts`\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/plugins/asset-pipeline.ts`\n- Test: `tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts` (already exists)\n\n**Step 1: Implement the plugin**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Plugin, ContentFile, BuildContext } from '../core/types.js';\n\nexport function createAssetPipelinePlugin(): Plugin {\n  return {\n    name: 'asset-pipeline',\n    version: '1.0.0',\n    dependencies: [],\n    hooks: {\n      transformContent: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext): ContentFile => {\n        const manifest = (ctx.data.get('asset-manifest') as { assets: string[] }) || { assets: [] };\n        const assetRegex = /(src|href)=\"\\.\\/([^\"]+)\"/g;\n\n        const content = file.content.replace(assetRegex, (_match, attr, path) => {\n          if (!manifest.assets.includes(path)) {\n            manifest.assets.push(path);\n          }\n          return `${attr}=\"/assets/${path}\"`;\n        });\n\n        ctx.data.set('asset-manifest', manifest);\n        return { ...file, content };\n      },\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Key details:**\n- Regex matches `src=\"./...\"` and `href=\"./...\"` patterns\n- Rewrites to `/assets/filename`\n- Accumulates assets in `ctx.data['asset-manifest']` across calls\n- Already-rewritten `/assets/` URLs don't match `./` pattern, so no double-processing\n- Absolute URLs (`https://...`) don't match `./` pattern\n\n**Step 2: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts\n```\n\nExpected: 8 tests pass.\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Create `src/plugins/syntax-highlight.ts`\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/plugins/syntax-highlight.ts`\n- Test: `tests/plugins/syntax-highlight.test.ts` (already exists)\n\n**Step 1: Implement the plugin**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Plugin, ContentFile, BuildContext } from '../core/types.js';\n\nexport function createSyntaxHighlightPlugin(): Plugin {\n  return {\n    name: 'syntax-highlight',\n    version: '1.0.0',\n    dependencies: [],\n    hooks: {\n      transformContent: (file: ContentFile, _ctx: BuildContext): ContentFile => {\n        const content = file.content.replace(\n          /<pre><code class=\"language-(\\w+)\">([\\s\\S]*?)<\\/code><\\/pre>/g,\n          (_match, lang, code) => {\n            return `<pre data-language=\"${lang}\"><code class=\"language-${lang} highlighted\">${code}</code></pre>`;\n          }\n        );\n        return { ...file, content };\n      },\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Key details:**\n- Only matches `<pre><code class=\"language-xxx\">` pattern\n- Adds `highlighted` class to `<code>` element\n- Adds `data-language=\"xxx\"` attribute to `<pre>` element\n- Inline `<code>` tags (not inside `<pre>`) are not matched\n- Plain `<code>` without `language-` class not matched\n\n**Step 2: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run tests/plugins/syntax-highlight.test.ts\n```\n\nExpected: 8 tests pass.\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Create `src/plugins/taxonomy.ts`\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/plugins/taxonomy.ts`\n- Test: `tests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts` (already exists)\n\n**Step 1: Implement the plugin**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Plugin, BuildContext, ContentFile } from '../core/types.js';\n\nexport function createTaxonomyPlugin(): Plugin {\n  return {\n    name: 'taxonomy',\n    version: '1.0.0',\n    dependencies: [],\n    hooks: {\n      beforeBuild: (ctx: BuildContext): void => {\n        const tagMap = new Map<string, ContentFile[]>();\n\n        for (const file of ctx.files) {\n          if (!file.tags) continue;\n          for (const tag of file.tags) {\n            const normalized = tag.toLowerCase();\n            if (!tagMap.has(normalized)) {\n              tagMap.set(normalized, []);\n            }\n            tagMap.get(normalized)!.push(file);\n          }\n        }\n\n        ctx.data.set('taxonomy-tags', tagMap);\n      },\n\n      afterBuild: (ctx: BuildContext): void => {\n        const tagMap = ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags') as Map<string, ContentFile[]>;\n        if (!tagMap) return;\n\n        for (const [tag, files] of tagMap) {\n          const items = files.map(f => `<li>${f.title}</li>`).join('\\n');\n          const html = `<h1>Tag: ${tag}</h1>\\n<ul>\\n${items}\\n</ul>`;\n          ctx.output.set(`tags/${tag}.html`, html);\n        }\n      },\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Key details:**\n- `beforeBuild`: Scans `ctx.files` for tags, normalizes to lowercase, builds `Map<string, ContentFile[]>`\n- Stores in `ctx.data` as `taxonomy-tags`\n- `afterBuild`: Iterates tag map, generates HTML listing pages at `tags/{tag}.html`\n- Files without tags are skipped\n- Multiple tags on same file → file appears under each tag\n\n**Step 2: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run tests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts\n```\n\nExpected: 8 tests pass.\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Create `src/plugins/rss-feed.ts`\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/plugins/rss-feed.ts`\n- Test: `tests/plugins/rss-feed.test.ts` (already exists)\n\n**Step 1: Implement the plugin**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Plugin, BuildContext, ContentFile } from '../core/types.js';\n\nexport function createRssFeedPlugin(): Plugin {\n  return {\n    name: 'rss-feed',\n    version: '1.0.0',\n    dependencies: ['markdown-ext', 'taxonomy'],\n    hooks: {\n      afterBuild: (ctx: BuildContext): void => {\n        const sorted = [...ctx.files].sort((a, b) => {\n          const da = a.date ? new Date(a.date).getTime() : 0;\n          const db = b.date ? new Date(b.date).getTime() : 0;\n          return db - da;\n        });\n\n        const items = sorted.map(file => {\n          const categories = (file.tags || [])\n            .map(t => `      <category>${t}</category>`)\n            .join('\\n');\n\n          const pubDate = file.date ? `\\n      <pubDate>${file.date}</pubDate>` : '';\n\n          return `    <item>\n      <title>${file.title}</title>\n      <link>${ctx.config.baseUrl}/${file.slug}.html</link>${pubDate}\n      <description><![CDATA[${file.content}]]></description>\n${categories}\n    </item>`;\n        }).join('\\n');\n\n        const xml = `<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<rss version=\"2.0\">\n  <channel>\n    <title>${ctx.config.title}</title>\n    <link>${ctx.config.baseUrl}</link>\n${items}\n  </channel>\n</rss>`;\n\n        ctx.output.set('feed.xml', xml);\n      },\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Key details:**\n- Dependencies: `markdown-ext`, `taxonomy`\n- Sort files by date descending (newest first), no-date files go to end (getTime() = 0)\n- Content wrapped in `<![CDATA[...]]>`\n- Tags from file.tags as `<category>` elements\n- Skip `<pubDate>` entirely if no date (don't output \"undefined\")\n- Channel title from `ctx.config.title`, link from `ctx.config.baseUrl`\n\n**Step 2: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run tests/plugins/rss-feed.test.ts\n```\n\nExpected: 7 tests pass.\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Create `src/plugins/search-index.ts`\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/plugins/search-index.ts`\n- Test: `tests/plugins/search-index.test.ts` (already exists)\n\n**Step 1: Implement the plugin**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Plugin, BuildContext } from '../core/types.js';\n\nfunction stripHtml(html: string): string {\n  return html.replace(/<[^>]*>/g, '').trim();\n}\n\nexport function createSearchIndexPlugin(): Plugin {\n  return {\n    name: 'search-index',\n    version: '1.0.0',\n    dependencies: ['markdown-ext', 'syntax-highlight'],\n    hooks: {\n      afterBuild: (ctx: BuildContext): void => {\n        const index = ctx.files.map(file => {\n          const entry: Record<string, unknown> = {\n            slug: file.slug,\n            title: file.title,\n            content: stripHtml(file.content),\n          };\n          if (file.tags) {\n            entry.tags = file.tags;\n          }\n          return entry;\n        });\n\n        ctx.output.set('search-index.json', JSON.stringify(index));\n      },\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Key details:**\n- Dependencies: `markdown-ext`, `syntax-highlight`\n- Strip all HTML tags from content using regex\n- Include tags only if present on file\n- Output valid JSON array\n\n**Step 2: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run tests/plugins/search-index.test.ts\n```\n\nExpected: 7 tests pass.\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Create `src/plugins/sitemap.ts`\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/plugins/sitemap.ts`\n- Test: `tests/plugins/sitemap.test.ts` (already exists)\n\n**Step 1: Implement the plugin**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Plugin, BuildContext, ContentFile } from '../core/types.js';\n\nexport function createSitemapPlugin(): Plugin {\n  return {\n    name: 'sitemap',\n    version: '1.0.0',\n    dependencies: ['taxonomy', 'rss-feed'],\n    hooks: {\n      afterBuild: (ctx: BuildContext): void => {\n        const urls: string[] = [];\n\n        for (const [path] of ctx.output) {\n          if (path === 'sitemap.xml') continue;\n          urls.push(`${ctx.config.baseUrl}/${path}`);\n        }\n\n        const urlEntries = urls\n          .map(url => `  <url>\\n    <loc>${url}</loc>\\n  </url>`)\n          .join('\\n');\n\n        const xml = `<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<urlset xmlns=\"http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/0.9\">\n${urlEntries}\n</urlset>`;\n\n        ctx.output.set('sitemap.xml', xml);\n      },\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Key details:**\n- Dependencies: `taxonomy`, `rss-feed`\n- Iterates all entries in `ctx.output` (HTML pages, tag pages, feed.xml)\n- Skips `sitemap.xml` itself\n- Prefixes all paths with `config.baseUrl`\n- Proper XML structure with urlset namespace\n\n**Step 2: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run tests/plugins/sitemap.test.ts\n```\n\nExpected: 7 tests pass.\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Create `src/plugins/dev-server.ts`\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/plugins/dev-server.ts`\n- Test: `tests/plugins/dev-server.test.ts` (already exists)\n\n**Step 1: Implement the plugin**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Plugin, BuildContext } from '../core/types.js';\n\ninterface DevServerConfig {\n  port: number;\n  routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;\n  assetPaths: string[];\n  searchIndexPath: string;\n}\n\nexport function createDevServerPlugin(): Plugin {\n  return {\n    name: 'dev-server',\n    version: '1.0.0',\n    dependencies: ['asset-pipeline', 'search-index'],\n    hooks: {\n      afterBuild: (ctx: BuildContext): void => {\n        const manifest = ctx.data.get('asset-manifest') as { assets: string[] } | undefined;\n        const assetPaths = manifest ? manifest.assets : [];\n\n        const routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }> = [];\n\n        // Asset routes\n        for (const asset of assetPaths) {\n          routes.push({ path: `/assets/${asset}`, handler: 'asset' });\n        }\n\n        // Content routes\n        for (const [path] of ctx.output) {\n          if (path.endsWith('.html')) {\n            routes.push({ path: `/${path}`, handler: 'static' });\n          }\n        }\n\n        const config: DevServerConfig = {\n          port: 3000,\n          routes,\n          assetPaths,\n          searchIndexPath: '/search-index.json',\n        };\n\n        ctx.data.set('dev-server-config', config);\n      },\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Key details:**\n- Dependencies: `asset-pipeline`, `search-index`\n- Default port: 3000\n- Reads `asset-manifest` from ctx.data, gracefully handles missing data (empty array)\n- Creates routes for assets (handler: 'asset') and HTML files (handler: 'static')\n- Fixed searchIndexPath: '/search-index.json'\n- Stores config in `ctx.data['dev-server-config']`\n\n**Step 2: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run tests/plugins/dev-server.test.ts\n```\n\nExpected: 7 tests pass.\n\n---\n\n### Task 9: Run full test suite\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run\n```\n\nExpected: 75 tests pass (15 core + 60 plugin).\n\n### Task 10: Run build\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\nExpected: Clean compile.\n\n### Task 11: Run lint\n\n```bash\nnpm run lint\n```\n\nExpected: No errors.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":121,"cache_read_input_tokens":38851,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":121},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0c0876a9-0499-47ee-b17e-658fa944a2e8","uuid":"4a9ad216-9225-4ba0-8de8-d547d5d38526"}
